{{infobox country at games | NPC = CAF | NPCname = Comité National Paralympique Centrafricain | games = Paralympics | year = | flagcaption = [[Flag of the Central African Republic]] | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Central African Republic|competition=Summer Paralympics|begin_year=2004|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }} The '''[[Central African Republic]]''' made its [[Paralympic Games]] début at the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Athens]]. It sent a single athlete, [[Thibaut Bomaya]], to compete in [[powerlifting]]. The country also entered a single-man delegation at the [[2008 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Beijing]], where [[Rosel-Clemariot-Christian Nikoua]] competed in [[shot put]]. The Central African Republic has never taken part in the Winter Paralympics, and has never won a Paralympic medal.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=CAF&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Central African Republic at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref>
The Central African Republic will be taking part in the [[2012 Summer Paralympics]], and the [[Comité National Paralympique Centrafricain]] have chosen [[Bedford]] as the UK training base for its Paralympians.<ref>http://www.bedford.gov.uk/council_and_democracy/council_news/archived_news/february_2012/on_your_marks.aspx</ref>
