{{Infobox company |name = Concave |type = [[Privately held company|Private]] |foundation = |location = Manchester, UK |area_served = Worldwide |industry = [[Sport]] |products = Aura / Volt / Quantum / Halo / PTX / T2 |revenue = |num_employees = |homepage = {{URL|http://www.concave.com/}} {{Facebook|concavefootball|Concave Football Boots}} }}
The '''Concave Football Boot''' is a special boot designed to increase the 'sweet spot' (the area of the boot that makes contact with the ball) by approximately four times. It has evolved the games of [[Australian Football League]], [[Soccer]] and [[Rugby League]]. Independent testing at Deakin University has shown the boot increases power by between 8-15% and provides increased accuracy with a smaller margin of error. Concave also designed this new boot to [http://soccerlens.com/shirts/concave-pt-metatarsal-injuries/6456/ protect] the [[metatarsal]] bones.<ref name="Soccerlens - Metatarsal">[http://soccerlens.com/metatarsal/16159/ The Metatarsal], Metatarsal bone injuries in football.</ref> The upper of the boot contains a flexible layer of TPU ([[Thermoplastic polyurethane]]) and a reinforced cushioning foam composite called "MetaGuard".<ref name="technology">[http://soccerlens.com/shirts/concave-boots-hit-it-longer-faster-and-on-target/543/ SoccerLens], review of Concave football boot technology.</ref> Research and development was independently conducted by [[Monash University]] and Invetech Systems Pty. Ltd. in Australia. Strategic design thinking and industrial design of the concave device and each year’s boot model range was undertaken by Melbourne-based design group, [http://www.CobaltNiche.com/ CobaltNiche] who also created the brand design and related marketing material.<ref name="Cobalt Niche design awards">[http://ianwongresearch.blogspot.com.au/2013/10/premiers-design-awards-cobaltniche.html], CobaltNiche design awards</ref> The Concave company is globally oriented with offices in [[Manchester]] and [[Melbourne]].
==Investors and Endorsements== Concave has a number of high-profile investors and former professional footballers involved including former [[Liverpool F. C.]] manager [[Kenny Dalglish]] and a number of former Australian football representatives including [[Kevin Muscat]], [[Paul Trimboli]], [[Michael Petersen]], [[Oscar Crino]], [[Warren Spink]] and [[Alistair Edwards]]. Concave also has [[Australian Football League]] legends [[Ron Barassi]] and [[James Hird]] as investors and shareholders.
The boot has been worn by over 40 [[Premier League]] players with the most high-profile players being [[John O'Shea]], at that time playing for [[Manchester United]], who wore the Concave "Classic PT+" boots for the first time during the Premier League game against [[Chelsea F. C.|Chelsea]] at [[Stamford Bridge (stadium)|Stamford Bridge]].{{citation needed|date=August 2013}} [[Wes Brown]], another player for Manchester United, also wore the boots.<ref name="Wes Brown spotted wearing Concaves">[http://www.soccerbible.com/news/general/archive/2010/07/26/pre-season-football-boots-spotting-26-07-10.aspx], Showing Wes Brown photographed wearing Concave boots</ref> Triple [[National Premier Leagues Victoria]] [[National Premier Leagues Victoria Golden Boot|Golden Boot]] winner and [[South Melbourne FC]] striker Milos Lujic is also endorsed by the company, and wears the 'Volt' range.
==Distributors== Concave has retail and online distribution in UK, Australia, Japan, Indonesia, USA and Europe.
==External links== *[http://www.concave.com/ Concave Official Site] *[http://shop.concave.com/ Concave Online Store] *[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/columnists/brianmoore/2303581/Euro-2008-England%27s-absence-is-a-relief.html Telegraph article mentioning Concave boot] *[http://soccerlens.com/shirts/concave-pt-metatarsal-injuries/6456/ Soccerlens.com] Protection of metatarsal claims *[http://www.premiersdesignawards.org.au/entry/concave-quantum1-football-boot/ Premier Design Awards] Quantum1 Football Boot *[http://www.footy-boots.com/new-concave-football-boots-4559/ Footy-Boots Commentary] *{{Facebook|concavefootball|Concave Football Boots}} *{{instagram|concavefootball|Concave Football Boots}}
