{{infobox organization | name = Dartmouth Yacht Club | image = | caption = | abbreviation = DYC | formation = 1962 | location = 697 [[Nova Scotia Trunk 7|Windmill Road]], [[Dartmouth, Nova Scotia|Dartmouth]], [[Halifax Regional Municipality]], {{NS}} {{CAN}} | leader_title = Commodore | leader_name = | coor = | campus = Waterfront | free_label = Tag line | free = | status = active | purpose = advocate and public voice, educator and network for recreational and competitive sailors, coaches, volunteers and events | language = [[English language|English]], [[French language|French]] | colours = | nickname = | publictransit = On a bus route | affiliations = [[Canadian Canoe Association]], [[Britannia Yacht Club]] | website = [http://www.dyc.ns.ca DYC.ns.ca] }}
The '''Dartmouth Yacht Club''' is a [[yacht club]] located in [[Wright's Cove]] in [[Halifax Harbour]]'s [[Bedford Basin]], next to [[Burnside Industrial Park]] in [[Dartmouth, Nova Scotia|Dartmouth]], [[Nova Scotia]], [[Canada]]. The club has a history dating to 1962.
==Partnerships== The DYC has reciprocal agreements with other yacht clubs, e.g. [[Britannia Yacht Club]].
