{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = EEstadio Municipal Centenario Manuel Rivera Sánchez | nickname = Estadio Centenario | image = | caption = | fullname = Estadio Municipal Centenario Manuel Rivera Sánchez | location = [[Chimbote]], [[Peru]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = 2006 - 2007 | opened = June 30, 2007 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Municipality of Chimbote | operator = Municipality of Chimbote | surface = [[Artificial turf]] | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = <center>[[José Gálvez FBC]] ([[Primera División Peruana|First Division]])</center> | seating_capacity = <center>25,000 ([[football (soccer)|football]])</center> | dimensions = }}
'''Estadio Municipal Centenario Manuel Rivera Sánchez''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Chimbote]], [[Peru]]. It was inaugurated on June 30, 2007 with a friendly game between the Peru U-17 national football team and the Colombia U-17 national football team. Peru lost 4-2. It hosts the home games of [[José Gálvez FBC]]. The stadium has a capacity of 25,000 people. It replaced [[Estadio Manuel Gómez Arellano]].
