{{Infobox football biography | name = George Dublin | image = | fullname = George Dublin | height = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1977|2|11}} | birth_place = [[Antigua and Barbuda]] | currentclub = [[Antigua Barracuda FC]] | clubnumber = 17 | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1997–2002 | clubs1 = [[Hoppers FC]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2002–2006 | clubs2 = [[Joe Public F.C.|Joe Public]] | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 2006–2007 | clubs3 = [[Hoppers F.C.|Hoppers]] | caps3 = | goals3 = | years4 = 2007–2008 | clubs4 = [[Tobago United]] | caps4 = | goals4 = | years5 = 2007–2008 | clubs5 = → [[Hoppers F.C.|Hoppers]] (loan) | caps5 = | goals5 = | years6 = 2008–2011 | clubs6 = [[Hoppers F.C.|Hoppers]] | caps6 = | goals6 = | years7 = 2011–2013 | clubs7 = [[Antigua Barracuda FC]] | caps7 = 41 | goals7 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2000– | nationalteam1 = [[Antigua and Barbuda national football team|Antigua and Barbuda]] | nationalcaps1 = 59 | nationalgoals1 = 4 | pcupdate = August 20, 2012 | ntupdate = September 16, 2011 }}
'''George Dublin''' (born February 11, 1977) is an [[Antigua and Barbuda|Antiguan]] [[association football|footballer]], currently playing for [[Antigua Barracuda FC]] in the [[USL Professional Division]].
==Club career== Dublin began his career in his native Antigua and Barbuda with [[Hoppers FC]], before moving to Trinidad and Tobago with [[Joe Public F.C.|Joe Public]]. He was part of the Joe Public side which won the [[TT Pro League]] title in 2006. He moved to [[Tobago United]] in 2007, but spent just one season there before returning to Antigua to play for [[Hoppers F.C.|Hoppers]] in the [[Antigua and Barbuda Premier Division]].
In 2011, Dublin transferred to the new [[Antigua Barracuda FC]] team prior to its first season in the [[USL Professional Division]]. He made his debut for the Barracudas on April 17, 2011 in the team's first competitive game, a 2–1 loss to the [[Los Angeles Blues]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20121011022237/http://www.uslsoccer.com/stats/2011/2175592.html Los Angeles Blues at Antigua Barracuda FC 2:1]. uslsoccer.com</ref>
==International career== Nicknamed ''Sowa'', Dublin made his debut for [[Antigua and Barbuda national football team|Antigua and Barbuda]] in an April 2000 [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Bermuda national football team|Bermuda]] and has earned over 30 caps since. He played in 9 World Cup qualification games,<ref>{{FIFA player|177212}}</ref> and was part of the Antigua squad which took part in the final stages of the [[2010 Caribbean Championship]].
