==Invicta FC 29: Kaufman vs. Lehner== {{Infobox MMA event |name=Invicta FC 29: Kaufman vs. Lehner |image= |date=May 4, 2018 |venue=[[Scottish Rite Temple (Kansas City, Kansas)|Scottish Rite Temple]] |city=[[Kansas City, Missouri]] |attendance= |previousevent=Invicta FC 28: Mizuki vs. Jandiroba |followingevent=Invicta FC 30: Frey vs. Grusander }}
'''Invicta FC 29: Kaufman vs. Lehner''' was a mixed martial arts event headlined by [[Sarah Kaufman (fighter)|Sarah Kaufman]] vs. Katharina Lehner fighting for the vacant bantamweight championship. Lisa Spangler was set to fight Yaya Rincon but the week of the event, Rincon pulled out of the bout and was replaced by Sarah Kleczka. 19 year old Croatian prospect Adriana Vukovic was scheduled to make her debut at this event but an opponent was not found for her, pushing her debut back to a future event.
