==Invicta FC 27: Kaufman vs. Kianzad== {{Infobox MMA event |name=Invicta FC 27: Kaufman vs. Kianzad |image= |date=January 13, 2018 |venue=[[Scottish Rite Temple (Kansas City, Kansas)|Scottish Rite Temple]] |city=[[Kansas City, Missouri]] |attendance= |previousevent=Invicta FC 26: Porto vs. Niedzwiedz |followingevent=Invicta FC 28: Mizuki vs. Jandiroba }}
'''Invicta FC 27: Kaufman vs. Kianzad''' was a mixed martial arts event headlined by veteran [[Sarah Kaufman (fighter)|Sarah Kaufman]] returning to Invicta against Pannie Kianzad. On December 6, Invicta announced Kaufman had been signed to return for a headline bout. A strawweight bout between Mallory Martin and Tiffany Masters was made after being originally scheduled for Invicta FC 24.
===Results=== {{MMAevent}} {{MMAevent card|Main Card (UFC Fight Pass)}} {{MMAevent bout |Catchweight (136.7 lbs) |[[Sarah Kaufman (fighter)|Sarah Kaufman]] |def. |[[Pannie Kianzad]] |Decision (unanimous) (30-27, 30-27, 30-27) |3 |5:00 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Flyweight |[[Vanessa Porto]] |def. |Mariana Morais |Submission (rear-naked choke) |1 |4:19 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Strawweight |[[Sharon Jacobson]] |def. |Ashley Nichols |Decision (unanimous) (30-27, 29-28, 29-28) |3 |5:00 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Atomweight |[[Ashley Cummins]] |def. |Stephanie Alba |Decision (unanimous) (30-27, 30-27, 30-27) |3 |5:00 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Flyweight |Brogan Walker-Sanchez |def. |Cheri Muraski |Decision (split) (29-28, 28-29, 29-28) |3 |5:00 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Featherweight |[[Felicia Spencer]] |def. |Akeela Al-Hameed |Decision (unanimous) (30-27, 30-27, 30-27) |3 |5:00 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Catchweight (117.4 lbs) |Mallory Martin |def. |Tiffany Masters |TKO (punches) |2 |3:36 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Atomweight |Loma Lookboonmee |def. |Melissa Wang |Decision (unanimous) (29-27, 29-26, 29-26) |3 |5:00 |Lookboonmee was deducted a point for illegal knees. }} {{MMAevent bout |Strawweight |Helen Peralta |def. |Jade Ripley |TKO (punches) |1 |2:22 | }} {{MMAevent end|notes=yes}}
==Invicta FC 26: Maia vs. Niedwiedz== {{Infobox MMA event |name=Invicta FC 26: Maia vs. Niedwiedz |image= |date=December 8, 2017 |venue=[[Scottish Rite Temple (Kansas City, Kansas)|Scottish Rite Temple]] |city=[[Kansas City, Missouri]] |attendance= |previousevent=Invicta FC 25: Kunitskaya vs. Pa'aluhi |followingevent=Invicta FC 27: Kaufman vs. Kianzad }}
'''Invicta FC 26: Maia vs. Niedwiedz''' was a mixed martial arts event headlined by [[Jennifer Maia]] defending her flyweight championship against top contender Agnieszka Niedzwiedz. Vanessa Porto was scheduled to fight [[Jessica-Rose Clark]], but Clark accepted a fight with the UFC and was replaced by [[Milana Dudieva]]. On November 13, Invicta announced the signing of the undefeated [[Mackenzie Dern]] to debut against [[Kaline Medeiros]]. Janaisa Morandin was scheduled to fight [[Mizuki Inoue]], but Mizuki pulled out of the fight on November 27 and was replaced by Kinberly Novaes
===Results=== {{MMAevent}} {{MMAevent card|Main Card (UFC Fight Pass)}} {{MMAevent bout |Flyweight |[[Jennifer Maia]] (c) |def. |[[Agnieszka Niedźwiedź]] |Decision (unanimous) (49-46, 49-46, 49-46) |5 |5:00 |For the [[Invicta Fighting Championships#Flyweight Championship|Invicta FC Flyweight Championship]] }} {{MMAevent bout |Strawweight |[[Mackenzie Dern]] |def. |[[Kaline Medeiros]] |Submission (armbar) |3 |4:45 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Catchweight (121.6 lbs) |Janaisa Morandin |def. |Kinberly Novaes |Decision (unanimous) (30-27, 30-27, 30-27) |3 |5:00 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Catchweight (127.6 lbs) |[[Vanessa Porto]] |def. |[[Milana Dudieva]] |TKO (punch to the body) |3 |3:02 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Catchweight (117.6 lbs) |Virna Jandiroba |def. |[[Amy Montenegro]] |Submission (armbar) |1 |2:50 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Catchweight (106.3 lbs) |[[Amber Brown (fighter)|Amber Brown]] |def. |[[Tessa Simpson]] |Submission (armbar) |1 |0:50 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Flyweight |[[Karina Rodríguez]] |def. |[[Christine Ferea]] |Decision (unanimous) (30-27, 29-28, 29-28) |3 |5:00 | }} {{MMAevent bout |Strawweight |Kay Hansen |def. |Emilee Prince |Submission (armbar) |1 |1:23 | }} {{MMAevent end|notes=yes}}
