==Invicta FC 17: Evinger vs. Schneider== {{Infobox MMA event |name=Invicta FC 17: Evinger vs. Schneider |image= |date=May 7, 2016 |venue=[[OC Fair & Event Center]] |city=[[Costa Mesa, California]] |attendance= |previousevent=Invicta FC 16: Hamasaki vs. Brown |followingevent=Invicta FC 18: Grasso vs. Esquibel }}
'''Invicta FC 17: Evinger vs. Schneider''' was a mixed martial arts event that was headlined by an [[Invicta Fighting Championships#Bantamweight Championship|Invicta FC Bantamweight Championship]] bout as champion [[Tonya Evinger]] defends against [[Colleen Schneider]]. The co-main event will feature [[Livia Renata Souza|Lívia Renata Souza]] defending her [[Invicta Fighting Championships#Straweeight Championship|Invicta FC Strawweight Championship]] against [[Angela Hill (fighter)|Angela Hill]]. Aline Serrio was scheduled to fight [[Mizuki Inoue]] but Mizuki was replaced by Kaline Medeiros due to an injury in training. An atomweight bout between newcomers Tessa Simpson and Julia Jones was scheduled but removed from the card on the week of the event.
